<article id="post-784" class="post-784 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-in-the-news tag-ethnography tag-virtual-worlds">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://cgvw.ics.uci.edu/ethnography-and-virtual-worlds/" rel="bookmark">Ethnography and Virtual Worlds</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p><a href="http://press.princeton.edu/titles/9882.html"><img class="alignnone" title="Ethnography and Virtual Worlds" src="http://press.princeton.edu/images/k9882.gif" alt="" width="147" height="222" /></a></p>
<p>Tom Boellstorff, Bonnie Nardi and two other colleagues have published the book &#8220;<a href="http://press.princeton.edu/titles/9882.html" target="_blank">Ethnography and Virtual Worlds: A Handbook of Method</a>&#8220;. A great read for students, teachers, designers, and scholars interested in using ethnographic methods to study online virtual worlds.</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
